name: Shun Fa Roasted Chicken Duck Rice Noodle

reviews.text: Ordered this roasted duck rice for $5. Taste is above average, maybe they can give duck meat that with skin. Feeling like eating normal duck instead of roast duck. But I really love their chicken rice tbh.

Our favourite braise duck moved from Woodlands Street 11 to Keat hong.

Today me and wife went over from Woodlands for the first time since the moved away. Food is still as good and the stall owners still recognise us. Love it.

This plate only $4. If only normal chicken rice $3. Where to find this type of price. It‚Äôs cheap good and fast! Their duck noodle or kway teow also very nice. Definitely recommended. Locals would form a long queue during meal times but their service always very fast. Recommended :)
stall seller are rude and unfriendly, gave a snoop look when i was ordering roast chicken breast. pass me the items as if i owe him.

This is the BEST chicken rice I have tried in CCK area! Chicken is tender and cooked to the right texture, rice is very fragrance and not too oily with nice blend of garlic fragrance. The chicken rice is especially tasty when eaten with the well-loved self-made chilli sauce üëçüëçüëç The price is very reasonable at $2.80 only.. very honest and down-to-earth hawker preparing very tasty and affordable food for all! Highly recommended to all!!!
